   "source": [
    "Bayes's theorem is a mathematical concept that calculates the probability of an event based on prior knowledge of conditions that might be related to the event. It is particularly useful in situations where you have prior beliefs or probabilities and new evidence to update those beliefs.\n",
    "\n",
    "Bayes's theorem formula:\n",
    "\n",
    "P(A∣B)= \n",
    "P(B)\n",
    "P(B∣A)⋅P(A)\n",
    "​\n",
    "\n",
    "P(A∣B): Probability of event A occurring given evidence \n",
    "P(B∣A): Probability of evidence B occurring given event A.\n",
    "(A): Prior probability of event A.\n",
    "P(B): Total probability of evidence B.\n",
    "Example: Suppose you want to find the probability of having a particular medical condition (A) given the results of a diagnostic test (B). Bayes's theorem allows you to incorporate the accuracy of the test and the prior probability of having the condition to update your probability estimate."
   ]
  },
