    " A confidence interval is a range of values constructed from sample data that is likely to contain the true population parameter with a certain level of confidence. It provides a range of values rather than a single point estimate.\n",
    "\n",
    "To calculate a confidence interval for a population mean:\n",
    "\n",
    "Choose a confidence level (e.g., 95%).\n",
    "Find the critical value (z-score or t-score) corresponding to the chosen confidence level.\n",
    "Calculate the standard error of the mean (SEM) using the sample standard deviation and sample size.\n",
    "Compute the margin of error (MOE) by multiplying the critical value by the SEM.\n",
    "Construct the confidence interval by adding and subtracting the MOE from the sample mean.\n",
    "Example: Calculate a 95% confidence interval for the mean height of a sample of 100 individuals, where the sample mean is 68 inches, the sample standard deviation is 3 inches, and you use a z-score for the critical value."
   ]
  },
