    "To calculate a 95% confidence interval for a sample of data with a mean of 50 and a standard deviation of 5:\n",
    "\n",
    "Determine the sample size (let's assume it's sufficiently large).\n",
    "Choose a confidence level (e.g., 95%).\n",
    "Find the critical value for a 95% confidence interval using a z-table or calculator (for a normal distribution, the critical value is approximately 1.96).\n",
    "Calculate the margin of error (MOE) by multiplying the critical value by the standard error of the mean (SEM).\n",
    "=\n",
    "1.96\n",
    "×\n",
    "5\n",
    "MOE=1.96× \n",
    "n\n",
    "​\n",
    " \n",
    "5\n",
    "​\n",
    " \n",
    "Construct the confidence interval by adding and subtracting the MOE from the sample mean.\n",
    "=\n",
    "Sample Mean\n",
    "±\n",
    "CI=Sample Mean±MOE\n",
    "Interpretation: The 95% confidence interval for the population mean is [sample mean - MOE, sample mean + MOE]. In this case, it might be [47.02, 52.98], which means you are 95% confident that the true population mean falls within this interval."
   ]
